# Articles Reference Content

The definite article and agreement rules - the framework for understanding Greek nouns.

## Purpose

Show how Greek articles change to match their noun's gender, case, and number. The article is your guide to understanding any noun.

## Key Insight

Greek articles change to match their noun's gender, case, and number. Once you see the pattern, it becomes predictable.

---

## The Core Pattern (Hero Element)

<insight>
The article must AGREE with its noun in three ways:
- **Gender**: masculine / feminine / neuter
- **Case**: nominative / accusative / genitive
- **Number**: singular / plural

This is why "the" has so many forms!
</insight>

---

## Gender Hints (Compact Reference)

<quick-reference name="gender-hints">
<title>Spot gender by noun ending</title>

| Gender    | Common Endings |
|-----------|----------------|
| Masculine | -ος, -ας, -ης, -ές |
| Feminine  | -α, -η, -ση, -ξη |
| Neuter    | -ο, -ι, -μα |

</quick-reference>

